<h2>How It Works</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Developer opens a PR → GitHub fires a webhook to your server</li>
  <li>Server verifies the HMAC-SHA256 signature and fetches the PR diff</li>
  <li>Diff is sent to a local LLM via Ollama for review</li>
  <li>Bot posts a structured comment on the PR automatically</li>
</ol>

<b>Review sections:</b> 🐛 Bugs & Logic Errors · 🔒 Security Issues · ⚡ Performance · 💡 Suggestions · ✅ Summary

---

<h2>Tech Stack</h2>

<b>Python · FastAPI · Uvicorn · Ollama (qwen2.5-coder:7b) · GitHub Apps API · JWT Authentication · ngrok</b>

---

<h2>Project Structure</h2>

```
SentinelCodeAI/
├── main.py           # Webhook server & orchestrator
├── github_auth.py    # JWT + installation token auth
├── github_client.py  # Fetch diffs, post comments
├── reviewer.py       # LLM review logic
├── .env              # ⚠️ Never commit
└── private-key.pem   # ⚠️ Never commit
```

---

<h2>Setup</h2>

<b>Prerequisites:</b> Python 3.11+ · <a href="https://ollama.com">Ollama</a> · <a href="https://ngrok.com">ngrok</a> · GitHub account

<br/><br/>

<b>1. Clone & install</b>

```bash
git clone https://github.com/aminabk99/SentinelCodeAI
cd SentinelCodeAI
python -m venv venv && source venv/Scripts/activate
pip install fastapi uvicorn requests PyJWT cryptography python-dotenv
```

<b>2. Pull the model</b> (~4.7GB)

```bash
ollama pull qwen2.5-coder:7b
```

<b>3. Create a GitHub App</b>
<ul>
  <li>GitHub → Settings → Developer Settings → GitHub Apps → <b>New GitHub App</b></li>
  <li>Permissions: Pull requests (Read & Write), Contents (Read)</li>
  <li>Subscribe to: Pull request events</li>
  <li>Save your <b>App ID</b>, download your <b>Private Key</b> (.pem), set a <b>Webhook Secret</b></li>
  <li>Install the app on your test repo</li>
</ul>

<b>4. Configure `.env`</b>

```env
GITHUB_APP_ID=your_app_id
GITHUB_PRIVATE_KEY_PATH=private-key.pem
GITHUB_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_secret
OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434
OLLAMA_MODEL=qwen2.5-coder:7b
```

<b>5. Start everything</b> (3 terminals)

```bash
ollama serve                           # Terminal 1
uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8000  # Terminal 2
ngrok http 8000                        # Terminal 3
```

Update your GitHub App's Webhook URL to `https://your-ngrok-url.ngrok-free.dev/webhook`

<b>6. Test it</b>

Open a PR on any repo where the app is installed → the bot posts a review automatically.
<br/>
Verify at: `https://your-ngrok-url/health` → `{"status":"ok"}`

---

<h2>Hardest Part</h2>

<b>GitHub App authentication</b> — Apps use short-lived JWTs signed with an RSA private key, exchanged for installation-scoped tokens. Getting the timing right and debugging a silent 401 from a mismatched webhook secret took the most work.

---

<h2>Most Interesting</h2>

<b>How much the system prompt shapes output quality.</b> Tightening the prompt to enforce strict markdown sections and explicitly say "never hallucinate issues not in the diff" turned vague responses into genuinely useful reviews. The model's behavior is almost entirely defined by the instructions you give it.

---

<h2>Security</h2>

<ul>
  <li><code>.env</code> and <code>private-key.pem</code> are in <code>.gitignore</code> — never commit them</li>
  <li>All webhook requests verified with HMAC-SHA256 before processing</li>
  <li>If your private key or secret is ever exposed, regenerate immediately in GitHub App settings</li>
</ul>

---

